  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (NC-6 clean)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Eleven factors are fully assessed with achieved levels meeting or exceeding required levels. Two factors — Numerical solver error and Use error — are marked not-applicable with documented rationale: the commercial solver (ANSYS Fluent 2023R2) carries an independent V&V certificate covering solver-level correctness, and use-error controls are entirely governed by the sponsor's ISO 13485 quality management system outside the scope of this credibility assessment. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed across all assessed factors. Decision: Accepted based on complete structured evidence with no credibility gaps.",
